      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DALLAS DALE NZ (2) had to work when parked last start so it may pay to overlook that result. Had looked close to a win when runner-up in his previous two outings, leading from one spot wider to miss by 2.4m at this circuit and distance two back. Should get his chance from this advantageous draw. KING HIT NZ (10) led and faded to fifth at his latest appearance but had been making good progress prior with a win and a second from his previous two starts here. Draws for a soft run on the inside of the second line and if he gets the gaps can figure in the finish. LOUS DREAM NZ (3) showed improvement last time out and is building in fitness so could be competitive. ONEHANDONEBOUNCE (5) has been producing some solid efforts at Menangle including a third from this barrier two back. Respect.",
